This rule applies ONLY to the Uppingham website project.
It overrides and extends the global coding standards.

PROJECT CONTEXT

- Framework: Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- i18n: next-intl
- Design source: Figma
- Website type: Multi-campus, bilingual, SEO-first marketing website

LANGUAGE RULE

- All code must be written in English.
- All explanations, reasoning, and guidance must be written in Vietnamese.
- Never mix Vietnamese inside code.

FIGMA-FIRST RULE (CRITICAL)

- Figma is the single source of truth.
- Do NOT invent layout, spacing, typography, colors, or components.
- Each Figma section must map to a reusable Section component.
- If a design detail is unclear, implement the safest minimal version and add a TODO.

I18N RULES

- English is the default language.
- Vietnamese is optional and may fallback to English.
- All UI text must use next-intl translation keys.
- No hardcoded user-facing text is allowed.
- API data may be single-language initially.

ARCHITECTURE RULES

- Use Next.js App Router.
- Server Components by default.
- Use "use client" only when interaction, animation, or browser APIs are required.
- Pages must only compose components; no complex logic in pages.

DATA & API RULES

- Data must be accessed via a repository pattern.
- UI components must never fetch data directly.
- Support mock data when API is unavailable.
- Switching from mock to real API must not require UI changes.

STYLING RULES

- Tailwind CSS only.
- Always use cn() helper to merge classNames.
- No arbitrary spacing or colors unless explicitly defined in Figma.

SEO RULES

- One H1 per page.
- Correct heading hierarchy.
- Use semantic HTML.
- Pages must be SEO-ready by default.
- Multilingual pages must support language alternates.

PERFORMANCE RULES

- Optimize for Core Web Vitals (LCP, CLS, TBT).
- Avoid unnecessary client-side JavaScript.
- Dynamically import heavy components.
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion for animations.

OUTPUT EXPECTATION

- Always provide complete, production-ready code.
- Clearly specify file paths.
- Provide a short explanation in Vietnamese describing key decisions.
